  "text": "Other paramyxoviruses, such as measles virus have been scrutinized for their ability to decrease the prevalence of atopic disease and asthma. Industrialized countries where vaccines, antibiotics and anti-viral drugs are commonly used to prevent or treat infections reportedly are plagued by high incidences of asthma and atopy [CITATION_1] . In addition, rhinovirus infections, which are most prevalent in infants under 6 months old, have been suggested, along with RSV, to promote early Th1 responses [CITATION_2] .",
